\lim_{n \to \infty} a_{n} = a
\lim_{n \to \infty} b_{n} = b
\lim_{n \to \infty} \min\{a_{n},b_{n}\} = \min\{a,b\}
\min\{a_{n},b_{n}\} 
a_{n}
b_{n}
\lim_{n \to \infty} a_{n} = a
\lim_{n \to \infty} b_{n} = b
\min\{a,b\}
\max\left\{a_n,b_n\right\}=\frac{1}{2}(a_n+b_n)+\frac{1}{2}\left|a_n-b_n\right|
\min\left\{a_n,b_n\right\}=\frac{1}{2}(a_n+b_n)-\frac{1}{2}\left|a_n-b_n\right|
a_n\to a
b_n\to b
\min (a_n,b_n)=\frac{1}{2}(a_n+b_n-|a_n-b_n|)\to \frac{1}{2}(a+b-|a-b|)=\min (a,b).
